SummaryEnglish:
Led by a hot-shot young "natural", nine young women defy the male-dominated tradition of Japanese sports... not to create a League of their own, but to take on the boys on their own artificial turf and prove there's nothing a man can do that a woman canâ€™t do just as well!

The hallowed stadiums of Japanese baseball become a battlefield as the bats crack, the sweat flies and every hard-earned run becomes another step in the long road-trip to victory! Sizzling sports action and gripping drama intertwine as nine young women come together in the heat of athletic competition to become the Princess Nine!

1.SummaryEnglish: Hidehiko was a pitching legend and his daughter Ryo has inherited his gift, playing on the local sandlot she can strike out any challenger with ease.

2.TitleEnglish: A Baseball Team at a Prestigious Girl's School?
2.SummaryEnglish: A mysterious boy enters the batter's cage, taking up the challenge against Ryo; the next day, Ryo is offered a scholarship for a prestigious girls' school.

3.SummaryEnglish: Ryo gets to see Izumi play tennis for a while, but there are other important things on her mind, like her school interview.

4.SummaryEnglish: Coach Kido is asked to recruit a master athlete named Seira, who was once rumored to be Olympic-bound until she turned delinquent.

5.SummaryEnglish: Ryo tries to convince a girl named Koharu, who once mastered the Wave Motion Swing, to join Kisaragi's team.

6.SummaryEnglish: Two new girls, Mao and Yoko, might join the Kisaragi team, but Mao is too timid to catch the ball and Yoko's resume seems a bit fishy.

7.SummaryEnglish: The Kisaragi Girls' team is still one person short; their best hope lies with Izumi, the star tennis player, but she has less than zero interest in helping Ryo.

8.SummaryEnglish: Izumi issues a challenge to Ryo, pitting her batting against Ryo's pitching, and if Izumi wins, the Kisaragi Girls' Baseball team must disband.

9.SummaryEnglish: The time has come for Ryo and Izumi to have their showdown; Ryo has experience on her side, but Izumi has confidence, an unbeatable will, and some personal coaching from Takasugi.

10.SummaryEnglish: The Kisaragi girls are about to play their first real game as a team, but they're still one person short, which leads to team manager Nene stepping up to the plate.

11.SummaryEnglish: The Kisaragi girls must beat Rinkai High, one of the best teams in the country, to be allowed in the league.

12.SummaryEnglish: Ryo wants to know the secret behind her father's legendary pitch, the Lightning Ball; the only one who can teach her is Coach Kido, but he has her plowing up a vegetable garden by hand instead of practicing on the mound.

13.SummaryEnglish: The newly-formed Kisaragi team doesn't stand a chance against Rinkai, a veteran team that's over 100 members strong; if the girls want to win, it'll take a special kind of strategy that only they can pull off.

17.SummaryEnglish: As Ryo lies in a hospital bed, her life fading after saving two stranded children, the team comes together to be by her side.

18.SummaryEnglish: Kanako's father, who has always been against a girls' baseball team, is about to hold a meeting to decide the Kisaragi team's fate.

19.SummaryEnglish: The girls are all fired up and ready for training camp, but before they go, Izumi treats Takasugi to a homemade dinner along the riverbank at sunset.

20.SummaryEnglish: Everyone's working hard at training camp, except for Izumi, who is distracted by her knowledge of Takasugi and Ryo.

21.SummaryEnglish: Takasugi and Ryo take shelter from the rain in an old cabin, giving them the chance to speak their feelings.

22.SummaryEnglish: Yuki always kept to herself, rarely speaking to anyone but her little doll, Fifi; but now Fifi has gone missing, and to everyone's shock, Yuki is despondent, weeping genuine tears.

23.SummaryEnglish: The regional preliminaries have begun, and the Kisaragi girls' first opponent is Hori Private, a school full of thugs and bruisers.

24.SummaryEnglish: Though the girls are racking up win after win, Coach Kido and Seishiro can tell that something's not quite right with Ryo.

25.SummaryEnglish: The Kisaragi Girls are facing their biggest challenge yet, but are unable to focus; Koharu is worried about her father, and Ryo is still reeling from the night before.

26.SummaryEnglish: With their backs against the wall and any hope of victory fading fast, the girls' path becomes as clear as it's ever been: be truthful with each other, trust one another, and fight as hard as you can until the very end.
